Program: Discovery
Title: An earth made for life - part two
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrycd
Last Broadcast Date: 15 March 2003
Report from Greenland to find out what the first environment on Earth was like. Greenland is home to earth's oldest rocks, and it is here scientists are to trace the beginnings of the early earth and what it was like 3.8 billion years ago Presenter: Gabrielle Walker.